WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:10.093 --> 00:00:12.387
Three. two. one.

2
00:00:19.853 --> 00:00:22.355
-No. let me do it!
-No. let me do it.

3
00:00:29.529 --> 00:00:31.656
I think that was faster.

4
00:00:31.740 --> 00:00:33.158
Fast enough to win?

5
00:00:33.908 --> 00:00:35.243
It depends who we're racing.

6
00:00:37.996 --> 00:00:40.081
How much do Ma and Pa
owe Miss Henderson again?

7
00:00:40.165 --> 00:00:42.500
-Six dollars?
-Six dollars and thirty cents.

8
00:00:44.002 --> 00:00:46.588
I'll win the slingshot competition
and the ring toss.

9
00:00:46.671 --> 00:00:47.672
That's ten cents.

10
00:00:48.173 --> 00:00:50.884
You'll win the embroidery competition
and the essay contest.

11
00:00:50.967 --> 00:00:52.844
That one's worth a whole dollar.

12
00:00:52.927 --> 00:00:55.638
It won't make up all the debt.
but it'll make up some of it.

13
00:00:55.722 --> 00:00:56.723
Shh.

14
00:00:58.224 --> 00:01:00.060
I don't want them to know that we know.

15
00:01:00.143 --> 00:01:03.229
-I wanna win the money and surprise them.
-All right.

16
00:01:05.000 --> 00:01:11.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

17
00:01:12.822 --> 00:01:14.822
-Admiring your corn again?
-That's right.

18
00:01:14.866 --> 00:01:18.203
Next year we'll plant twice as much
and buy a milk cow

19
00:01:20.080 --> 00:01:21.748
and get to building a bigger house…

20
00:01:24.250 --> 00:01:25.585
One with bedrooms.

21
00:01:30.006 --> 00:01:31.841
Mortgage payments will come in
any day now.

22
00:01:32.425 --> 00:01:35.261
The crops will be in.
I'll do more winter hunting and trapping.

23
00:01:35.345 --> 00:01:38.306
We'll have plenty of furs to sell.
Dream big.

24
00:01:38.932 --> 00:01:41.976
I'll dream big when that mortgage
starts coming on time every month.

25
00:01:46.606 --> 00:01:49.109
-What do you think about a bigger house?
-Yes.

26
00:01:49.651 --> 00:01:50.860
We want a sleeping loft.

27
00:01:50.944 --> 00:01:54.656
-And a bookcase for our treasures.
-And a sitting room. And a stove.

28
00:01:55.240 --> 00:01:56.991
Never hurts to know what you want.

29
00:01:57.784 --> 00:01:59.869
Dream as big as the sky.
Make a plan to get it.

30
00:01:59.953 --> 00:02:02.497
All I'm dreaming about
right now is Founders Day.

31
00:02:02.580 --> 00:02:05.083
Our plan is to eat popcorn
and dance at the dance.

32
00:02:05.667 --> 00:02:06.668
Solid plan.

33
00:02:08.837 --> 00:02:09.837
I wanna dance.

34
00:02:32.694 --> 00:02:37.115
Independence is a town
named after a way of life.

35
00:02:37.615 --> 00:02:41.870
The families who came here
were hoping for freedom

36
00:02:41.953 --> 00:02:44.205
and a fresh start in a new place.

37
00:02:45.331 --> 00:02:47.251
You see. I much prefer your cobbler.

38
00:02:49.335 --> 00:02:51.504
I didn't know
that you could play the piano. Mr. Scott.

39
00:02:51.588 --> 00:02:52.505
Years of lessons.

40
00:02:52.589 --> 00:02:55.049
In the West. I'm all about the new songs.
Any requests?

41
00:02:56.467 --> 00:02:59.470
There's a raffle and kettle corn
and lemonade. Come on!

42
00:03:02.891 --> 00:03:04.976
Silly me.
thinking it would be a family day.

43
00:03:05.476 --> 00:03:08.313
It's hard to compete with lemonade.

44
00:03:08.396 --> 00:03:11.024
Not wrong about that.
It's good to see you both.

45
00:03:11.107 --> 00:03:12.108
Mm.

46
00:03:13.359 --> 00:03:15.528
I heard the Osage
are riding out next week.

47
00:03:15.612 --> 00:03:16.905
Most of them. yes.

48
00:03:18.281 --> 00:03:19.324
Will you go with them?

49
00:03:21.242 --> 00:03:22.994
-We haven't decided yet.
-No.

50
00:03:27.165 --> 00:03:29.292
We heard school's starting in September.

51
00:03:29.375 --> 00:03:32.337
Thank goodness.
The girls have had enough of my lessons.

52
00:03:32.921 --> 00:03:34.047
Oh.

53
00:03:34.130 --> 00:03:38.885
-I thought you'd be teaching.
-I don't know. I… I have my hands full.

54
00:03:39.385 --> 00:03:42.096
Ladies and gentlemen of Independence.

55
00:03:42.597 --> 00:03:44.599
may I have your attention. please?

56
00:03:45.725 --> 00:03:49.437
Let me be the first to wish you all…

57
00:03:53.650 --> 00:03:55.777
…a Happy Founders Day!

58
00:03:57.946 --> 00:03:59.197
Hit it. Scott!

59
00:04:11.251 --> 00:04:12.085
Here you go.

60
00:04:12.168 --> 00:04:15.004
The ring toss is at the same time
as the three-legged race.

61
00:04:15.088 --> 00:04:18.132
-You're not gonna be able to do both.
-I could enter the ring toss.

62
00:04:18.633 --> 00:04:20.593
If I win. I could give you my prize money.

63
00:04:21.177 --> 00:04:23.346
-You told her?
-She won't say anything.

64
00:04:23.429 --> 00:04:26.099
-We don't need help.
-We do need help.

65
00:04:26.182 --> 00:04:29.852
If we end up staying. you could teach me
how to make flower crowns.

66
00:04:29.936 --> 00:04:31.271
Then we'll be even.

67
00:04:33.815 --> 00:04:34.983
That's fair.

68
00:04:35.066 --> 00:04:38.820
Pa says to dream as big as the sky.
and then make a plan to get it.

69
00:04:42.407 --> 00:04:43.533
So let's go get it.

70
00:04:46.244 --> 00:04:48.079
And no one knows where he went?

71
00:04:48.162 --> 00:04:52.333
Apparently. he asked Dr. Blake
in Elk City to take on his patients.

72
00:04:52.417 --> 00:04:55.044
and then he rode
right off the face of the earth.

73
00:04:56.838 --> 00:04:59.132
-Haven't heard anything since.
-Mm-hmm.

74
00:05:00.216 --> 00:05:02.051
Maybe he went back to his wife.

75
00:05:02.593 --> 00:05:05.013
-Why would you…
-Or maybe he went off to divorce her.

76
00:05:05.096 --> 00:05:06.764
It's 50-50. At least now you know.

77
00:05:06.848 --> 00:05:10.226
Know what? I don't know anything
except that he was untruthful.

78
00:05:10.310 --> 00:05:12.979
I wouldn't give up on him. not yet.

79
00:05:13.062 --> 00:05:15.189
-Since when are you an optimist?
-Uh…

80
00:05:16.232 --> 00:05:17.775
-I am not an optimist.
-Mm-hmm.

81
00:05:17.859 --> 00:05:19.736
I just know a girl in love when I see her.

82
00:05:19.819 --> 00:05:21.404
Who said anything about love?

83
00:05:25.950 --> 00:05:27.368
Oh. we're almost out.

84
00:05:29.078 --> 00:05:31.414
Do you want to go
shoot some holes in this barrel?

85
00:05:31.497 --> 00:05:34.292
I always feel so much better
when I shoot holes in things.

86
00:05:34.375 --> 00:05:35.752
No. No. thank you.

87
00:05:39.964 --> 00:05:40.840
How romantic.

88
00:05:40.923 --> 00:05:42.175
Mind if I borrow her?

89
00:05:42.258 --> 00:05:44.135
Go on. I'll finish up here.

90
00:05:47.305 --> 00:05:49.366
Why'd you tell him
we hadn't decided yet?

91
00:05:49.390 --> 00:05:50.558
Because we haven't.

92
00:05:51.809 --> 00:05:54.812
You've said you didn't wanna walk away
from everything we've built here.

93
00:05:54.896 --> 00:05:56.356
so what changed?

94
00:05:56.439 --> 00:05:58.649
I felt like I made
a difference at the signing.

95
00:05:58.733 --> 00:06:02.362
I'd like to keep doing that. Translating.
negotiating. looking out for our future.

96
00:06:02.445 --> 00:06:05.823
Your father wouldn't like it. not after
everything you put into the house.

97
00:06:05.907 --> 00:06:07.658
I don't care what my father likes.

98
00:06:08.242 --> 00:06:11.371
It was one thing when the land was
in limbo. but the deal is done.

99
00:06:12.080 --> 00:06:15.208
I'm afraid we won't be welcome.
We won't be safe.

100
00:06:15.291 --> 00:06:17.919
-On our own land?
-That's not how they'll see it.

101
00:06:19.921 --> 00:06:21.839
Louis said he'd buy
the house and the farm.

102
00:06:21.923 --> 00:06:24.801
Maybe starting over
will be the best thing for all of us.

103
00:06:31.766 --> 00:06:32.975
All of us.

104
00:06:36.854 --> 00:06:38.773
So you just wanna leave Julia here.

105
00:06:41.067 --> 00:06:42.777
She'll always be with us.

106
00:06:55.206 --> 00:06:58.126
-Happy Founders Day to y'all.
-Happy Founders Day.

107
00:07:00.169 --> 00:07:03.297
-You told me the money would come.
-It's from my father.

108
00:07:06.217 --> 00:07:07.802
He put Carrie's name in the Bible.

109
00:07:15.017 --> 00:07:16.017
What?

110
00:07:19.021 --> 00:07:20.314
Mr. Gustafson had a stroke.

111
00:07:20.982 --> 00:07:23.734
-Oh no.
-He's alive. He's still recovering.

112
00:07:23.818 --> 00:07:26.821
His wife says they can start payments
once their son comes to help.

113
00:07:26.904 --> 00:07:28.781
but that would be long after the harvest.

114
00:07:28.865 --> 00:07:31.325
-No money for a year?
-At least.

115
00:07:33.453 --> 00:07:36.998
The girls need new clothes.
new shoes. books for school.

116
00:07:37.498 --> 00:07:40.042
We're already low
on cornmeal. flour. beans.

117
00:07:40.960 --> 00:07:42.044
And we're in debt.

118
00:07:42.128 --> 00:07:44.046
I hate kicking a sick man
out of his house.

119
00:07:44.130 --> 00:07:46.924
but we could repossess.
look for a new buyer.

120
00:07:49.010 --> 00:07:50.690
I'd have to go back to get things settled.

121
00:07:51.345 --> 00:07:54.182
Even if we had money for the trip.
I… I can't be here alone. Charles.

122
00:08:04.650 --> 00:08:06.319
I need to get that teaching job.

123
00:08:06.903 --> 00:08:07.987
What about Carrie?

124
00:08:08.070 --> 00:08:11.407
I'll find someone to watch her.
Or I'll bring her with me.

125
00:08:12.825 --> 00:08:14.368
This town's growing like a weed.

126
00:08:14.869 --> 00:08:17.163
They'll need good carpenters
before the snow comes.

127
00:08:17.872 --> 00:08:20.416
Every time Eli James opens his mouth.
it's about that railroad.

128
00:08:20.500 --> 00:08:21.792
There must be jobs there.

129
00:08:23.544 --> 00:08:24.629
Something will turn up.

130
00:08:32.094 --> 00:08:33.094
Dream big.

131
00:08:44.941 --> 00:08:47.276
On your mark. get set.

132
00:08:48.611 --> 00:08:49.487
go!

133
00:08:53.282 --> 00:08:55.010
Go. go. go!

134
00:08:55.034 --> 00:08:56.118
-You got it!
-Come on!

135
00:09:00.790 --> 00:09:02.208
We have our winner!

136
00:09:03.459 --> 00:09:04.460
Bravo!

137
00:09:06.420 --> 00:09:08.548
All right. let's go.

138
00:09:08.631 --> 00:09:10.174
-Good job. girls.
-Come on!

139
00:09:12.927 --> 00:09:14.637
You must've been a good father.

140
00:09:16.639 --> 00:09:17.890
I tried.

141
00:09:21.561 --> 00:09:23.229
They were lucky to have you.

142
00:09:31.571 --> 00:09:33.614
Okay. enough slush.

143
00:09:33.698 --> 00:09:36.200
I have a slingshot competition to judge.

144
00:09:44.417 --> 00:09:46.544
Both of you pull at the same time.

145
00:09:47.044 --> 00:09:49.672
No. pull together.
You're pulling separately.

146
00:09:49.755 --> 00:09:52.883
Okay. now hold on the left.
And on the right…

147
00:09:53.384 --> 00:09:54.760
Okay. it's… it's… Oh!

148
00:09:56.512 --> 00:09:58.055
It's a spectacular day.

149
00:09:58.139 --> 00:09:59.932
I did have a vision. didn't I?

150
00:10:00.016 --> 00:10:01.142
Yes.

151
00:10:01.726 --> 00:10:05.855
I hear Mary is Romanzy's big competition
for the essay contest.

152
00:10:05.938 --> 00:10:08.899
I haven't heard a word of it.
but she's been practicing for weeks.

153
00:10:08.983 --> 00:10:10.818
Oh! May the best speaker win.

154
00:10:13.321 --> 00:10:15.573
I've been thinking
about how much I miss teaching.

155
00:10:15.656 --> 00:10:19.201
Higher on the right side.
Exactly. like that. Hold it. Hold it.

156
00:10:19.285 --> 00:10:21.329
Perfect.

157
00:10:23.247 --> 00:10:24.749
I'm sorry. you were saying?

158
00:10:24.832 --> 00:10:28.127
I… I'd like to take the teaching position
when the term starts.

159
00:10:28.628 --> 00:10:33.049
Caroline. that position's been filled.
A young woman Margaret recommended.

160
00:10:33.549 --> 00:10:37.470
She has two years' experience
and comes with very high marks.

161
00:10:37.970 --> 00:10:38.970
Oh.

162
00:10:39.680 --> 00:10:42.099
You know teaching's for unmarried women.

163
00:10:42.183 --> 00:10:44.560
Those are not my rules.
They're just the rules.

164
00:10:44.644 --> 00:10:47.521
You've got your baby and your family.

165
00:10:48.022 --> 00:10:52.151
And I'm sure you'll agree
this town needs as many young. fresh faces

166
00:10:52.234 --> 00:10:53.653
as we can tempt.

167
00:10:53.736 --> 00:10:55.029
Of course.

168
00:10:56.781 --> 00:10:59.325
Besides. I've got something else for you.

169
00:11:00.660 --> 00:11:01.911
Once the railroad comes in.

170
00:11:01.994 --> 00:11:04.872
I'll be entertaining
and hosting new arrivals.

171
00:11:05.373 --> 00:11:07.500
Eli is planning to run
for mayor.

172
00:11:07.583 --> 00:11:09.752
That's a secret. Don't say a word.

173
00:11:10.252 --> 00:11:12.213
I'll have my hands absolutely full.

174
00:11:12.296 --> 00:11:15.299
which means I won't have
much time for the Women's Society.

175
00:11:16.425 --> 00:11:17.677
I'd like you to take it on.

176
00:11:18.386 --> 00:11:22.014
I'd still be the director. of course.
but you'd manage the day-to-day.

177
00:11:24.475 --> 00:11:25.643
The women look up to you.

178
00:11:27.603 --> 00:11:28.688
I'm flattered.

179
00:11:30.022 --> 00:11:32.024
Unfortunately. I need paid work right now.

180
00:11:33.401 --> 00:11:34.985
Oh. I didn't realize.

181
00:11:39.281 --> 00:11:40.866
I'll let you get on with your day.

182
00:11:46.831 --> 00:11:50.251
The Judson's planning to expand
their restaurant and bakery.

183
00:11:50.876 --> 00:11:53.003
They'll be looking for an excellent cook.

184
00:11:53.087 --> 00:11:55.464
I'd be happy to recommend you.
if that's of interest.

185
00:11:57.591 --> 00:11:59.176
Yes. thank you.

186
00:11:59.260 --> 00:12:02.221
And you'll let me know
about the Women's Society?

187
00:12:03.097 --> 00:12:06.100
You'd want a working woman
to head your society?

188
00:12:07.435 --> 00:12:09.520
We're all working women. aren't we?

189
00:12:16.026 --> 00:12:20.322
I was wondering.
now that the treaty is signed.

190
00:12:21.073 --> 00:12:23.367
if the town might be getting
some railroad work.

191
00:12:24.076 --> 00:12:25.119
If so.

192
00:12:26.454 --> 00:12:28.664
I'd appreciate you putting in
a good word for me.

193
00:12:29.206 --> 00:12:30.624
There certainly is work.

194
00:12:30.708 --> 00:12:33.878
and I'd be happy to recommend you
as a potential foreman.

195
00:12:34.378 --> 00:12:36.088
We could use a man like you.

196
00:12:37.006 --> 00:12:38.006
Thank you.

197
00:12:38.340 --> 00:12:42.803
Of course. a railroad
in Independence will take some time.

198
00:12:43.512 --> 00:12:46.223
but there's plenty available
on the extension lines.

199
00:12:46.307 --> 00:12:48.934
Could be Nebraska.
or. more likely. Colorado.

200
00:12:54.190 --> 00:12:56.918
I don't know if I like the idea
of being that far away from my family.

201
00:12:56.942 --> 00:12:59.236
It would only be for a year or so.

202
00:13:00.154 --> 00:13:02.948
I'll imagine you've got
big plans for that land.

203
00:13:03.449 --> 00:13:05.576
-Yes.
-Think about it.

204
00:13:06.285 --> 00:13:08.412
Now I need to go see about my girls.

205
00:13:08.496 --> 00:13:12.875
They have a knack for finding trouble.
They get that from Jemma. not me.

206
00:13:16.962 --> 00:13:20.049
I am pleased to announce
that our first-prize winner

207
00:13:20.132 --> 00:13:25.554
for excellent design.
color choice. and stitch work is…

208
00:13:29.725 --> 00:13:32.353
Mary Ingalls.

209
00:13:32.436 --> 00:13:34.522
-Thank you.
-Well done.

210
00:13:37.358 --> 00:13:39.318
Excellent work. Very good.

211
00:13:50.579 --> 00:13:52.289
Congratulations.

212
00:13:52.373 --> 00:13:55.376
Thank you. You won something too?

213
00:13:55.960 --> 00:13:58.754
Gingersnaps. first prize.
Didn't have much competition.

214
00:14:02.550 --> 00:14:04.468
I haven't seen Caleb anywhere.

215
00:14:05.594 --> 00:14:07.763
He was a little down this morning.

216
00:14:08.597 --> 00:14:09.890
Wouldn't tell me why.

217
00:14:12.101 --> 00:14:13.811
Maybe you can find him. cheer him up?

218
00:14:21.151 --> 00:14:22.361
Thank you. ladies.

219
00:14:28.534 --> 00:14:29.534
Hello.

220
00:14:31.412 --> 00:14:32.955
Dr. Tann. welcome back.

221
00:14:34.248 --> 00:14:37.501
-I was hoping we could. uh. talk.
-Well. I need to get going.

222
00:14:38.961 --> 00:14:40.713
I don't require company. thank you.

223
00:14:41.213 --> 00:14:44.425
-I'm just back from Philadelphia.
-Well. I hope you had a nice trip.

224
00:14:44.925 --> 00:14:48.012
-Emily. I'd like to explain.
-There's no need. A no is a no.

225
00:14:48.095 --> 00:14:50.973
I sent divorce papers home
just after our Christmas.

226
00:14:52.808 --> 00:14:54.435
My wife wouldn't sign them.

227
00:14:56.687 --> 00:14:57.687
I see.

228
00:14:59.690 --> 00:15:01.400
When you asked about the future.

229
00:15:02.568 --> 00:15:05.029
I knew I had to go
and get it settled immediately.

230
00:15:09.575 --> 00:15:10.575
So I did.

231
00:15:13.954 --> 00:15:14.954
Hm.

232
00:15:16.040 --> 00:15:17.040
Enjoy your day.

233
00:15:22.588 --> 00:15:23.631
Want some?

234
00:15:24.214 --> 00:15:26.383
Fought off Old Man Spencer
for the last of it.

235
00:15:27.551 --> 00:15:29.553
It's fine.
He doesn't have any teeth anyway.

236
00:15:35.476 --> 00:15:36.560
Cheer up.

237
00:15:36.644 --> 00:15:39.897
It's Founders Day.
Two years of Independence.

238
00:15:39.980 --> 00:15:42.608
Sam Parker just told me a crew
of young men came into town

239
00:15:42.691 --> 00:15:44.360
to work construction last week.

240
00:15:45.402 --> 00:15:46.445
charging half the rate.

241
00:15:47.279 --> 00:15:48.279
Half the rate?

242
00:15:48.948 --> 00:15:51.033
They even know one end
of a hammer from the other?

243
00:15:51.533 --> 00:15:52.533
Does it matter?

244
00:15:57.331 --> 00:16:00.042
The couple that bought our land
in Wisconsin just defaulted.

245
00:16:02.378 --> 00:16:05.130
Thought I might try to pick up
construction work this fall. but…

246
00:16:06.924 --> 00:16:08.342
I just can't seem to get ahead.

247
00:16:12.513 --> 00:16:16.308
I have a spot of work chasing strays
on a cattle drive coming up.

248
00:16:17.101 --> 00:16:18.227
Happy to split the job.

249
00:16:20.020 --> 00:16:22.064
Probably give you a milk cow for free.

250
00:16:22.147 --> 00:16:24.525
The calves.
they struggle to keep up with the herd.

251
00:16:25.442 --> 00:16:27.611
Sure your girls
would love some fresh butter.

252
00:16:28.362 --> 00:16:31.365
-Now. that's generous.
-Nah. purely selfish.

253
00:16:31.949 --> 00:16:34.660
If you don't stick around.
you don't help me build my house.

254
00:16:36.829 --> 00:16:39.832
-A house?
-Hm. Things are settled with the land.

255
00:16:41.083 --> 00:16:42.083
Figured

256
00:16:43.544 --> 00:16:44.962
maybe I should get settled too.

257
00:16:48.257 --> 00:16:50.801
Look. don't worry about those young men
and their cheap work.

258
00:16:50.884 --> 00:16:54.346
First gust or gale that hits.
people want good work from professionals.

259
00:16:57.725 --> 00:17:00.394
What do you say we go
into this rail-splitting competition.

260
00:17:00.894 --> 00:17:02.354
show these young men who's boss?

261
00:17:07.359 --> 00:17:09.278
Hi. Laura. Who's your friend?

262
00:17:10.154 --> 00:17:11.405
This is Good Eagle.

263
00:17:12.614 --> 00:17:15.117
Good Eagle. this is Edith and Romanzy.

264
00:17:15.200 --> 00:17:19.872
-How come you never came to play with us?
-You were mean about Caleb. That's why.

265
00:17:20.456 --> 00:17:21.957
Have you finally learned to read?

266
00:17:22.041 --> 00:17:24.835
Or will you have to sit with the babies
when school starts?

267
00:17:26.253 --> 00:17:27.337
I can read.

268
00:17:27.921 --> 00:17:30.382
Next competitor. step forward.

269
00:17:46.607 --> 00:17:50.110
So I guess you were lying about being able
to hit a rabbit from 20 paces.

270
00:18:23.310 --> 00:18:25.187
I won the embroidery contest.

271
00:18:25.979 --> 00:18:27.981
You should've seen Romanzy's face.

272
00:18:29.608 --> 00:18:30.901
Congratulations.

273
00:18:35.531 --> 00:18:36.698
Are you all right?

274
00:18:40.994 --> 00:18:41.995
You got a letter.

275
00:18:44.456 --> 00:18:45.456
From my mother.

276
00:18:46.416 --> 00:18:47.416
Your mother?

277
00:18:47.835 --> 00:18:51.630
After Christmas. Emily put notices
in newspapers all over the country.

278
00:18:51.713 --> 00:18:54.091
My mother saw one. and she wrote to me.

279
00:18:54.716 --> 00:18:57.469
She said that she didn't know
what had happened to me.

280
00:18:57.553 --> 00:19:00.347
She's living in Cincinnati now.
and she wants me to come home.

281
00:19:02.599 --> 00:19:03.725
Oh.

282
00:19:04.309 --> 00:19:06.145
I wanna see her more than anything.

283
00:19:06.895 --> 00:19:09.231
But what if Emily gets upset
at me for leaving?

284
00:19:10.357 --> 00:19:11.942
Emily won't be upset.

285
00:19:13.235 --> 00:19:14.361
She'll miss you.

286
00:19:16.613 --> 00:19:17.698
But she won't be upset.

287
00:19:18.615 --> 00:19:19.741
What about you?

288
00:19:23.620 --> 00:19:25.164
Family is everything.

289
00:19:27.124 --> 00:19:28.542
I want you to have that.

290
00:19:40.387 --> 00:19:41.555
But I'll miss you too.

291
00:19:45.559 --> 00:19:48.979
Independence. the word.
stands for freedom and self-sufficiency.

292
00:19:49.062 --> 00:19:52.524
And Independence. the town.
stands for those same values.

293
00:19:52.608 --> 00:19:55.152
I don't want to go to school next year.

294
00:19:55.235 --> 00:19:56.778
Forget about those girls.

295
00:19:57.279 --> 00:19:58.279
We'll sit together.

296
00:19:58.322 --> 00:20:01.283
and no one will bother us
'cause we're smarter than all of them.

297
00:20:01.366 --> 00:20:03.952
You don't even know if you're staying yet.

298
00:20:05.913 --> 00:20:07.748
I might be all alone next year.

299
00:20:08.332 --> 00:20:11.001
You have your sister.
You'll never be alone.

300
00:20:13.337 --> 00:20:14.337
You're right.

301
00:20:15.172 --> 00:20:17.382
…for other
like-minded individuals.

302
00:20:18.091 --> 00:20:19.843
His hard work paid off.

303
00:20:19.927 --> 00:20:22.387
Our town is more than Independence.

304
00:20:22.971 --> 00:20:24.014
It is home.

305
00:20:30.979 --> 00:20:32.022
First.

306
00:20:33.273 --> 00:20:35.817
Well done. Romanzy James.

307
00:20:36.318 --> 00:20:39.446
Last but not least. Mary Ingalls.

308
00:20:44.701 --> 00:20:46.328
Miss Ingalls?

309
00:20:49.414 --> 00:20:51.416
-You should go up there.
-Miss Ingalls?

310
00:20:51.500 --> 00:20:54.753
-No. Mary's the smart one.
-Last call for Miss Ingalls.

311
00:20:54.836 --> 00:20:56.171
You're just as smart.

312
00:20:57.589 --> 00:21:00.300
Then the competition is concluded.

313
00:21:00.801 --> 00:21:01.843
Wait!

314
00:21:03.762 --> 00:21:04.763
I'm Miss Ingalls.

315
00:21:31.290 --> 00:21:32.833
Independence…

316
00:21:34.876 --> 00:21:37.421
Is a town named after a way of life.

317
00:21:45.762 --> 00:21:49.182
Independence is actually
a funny name for a town like this.

318
00:21:50.100 --> 00:21:53.979
The prairie is so big. and we're so small.

319
00:21:56.023 --> 00:21:57.190
The truth is

320
00:21:58.775 --> 00:22:00.944
none of us can make it alone here.

321
00:22:03.238 --> 00:22:04.740
We need help from each other

322
00:22:05.365 --> 00:22:07.117
when we need a place to live

323
00:22:07.909 --> 00:22:09.619
and when we get sick

324
00:22:10.370 --> 00:22:11.830
and when we get lonely.

325
00:22:13.665 --> 00:22:17.210
Independence isn't about self-reliance

326
00:22:17.294 --> 00:22:21.798
or liberty or freedom
or any of those things.

327
00:22:21.882 --> 00:22:24.092
It's a place to come together.

328
00:22:25.594 --> 00:22:27.971
a place to find out who you really are.

329
00:22:28.972 --> 00:22:33.185
Independence means getting to know
people who have been here a long time

330
00:22:33.268 --> 00:22:35.812
or people who have just arrived.

331
00:22:35.896 --> 00:22:38.940
people who are different
from anyone you've known before

332
00:22:39.566 --> 00:22:41.735
or people who feel like family.

333
00:22:44.613 --> 00:22:48.283
Independence isn't really a place.

334
00:22:49.284 --> 00:22:50.494
It's an idea.

335
00:22:51.119 --> 00:22:53.872
It's the people
you carry around in your heart.

336
00:22:59.044 --> 00:23:01.254
Good job. Laura!

337
00:23:01.338 --> 00:23:02.756
Good job. Laura!

338
00:23:02.839 --> 00:23:04.007
-Whoo!
-Yeah!

339
00:23:04.091 --> 00:23:05.384
Bravo!

340
00:23:05.967 --> 00:23:07.969
Amazing speech!

341
00:23:08.053 --> 00:23:09.054
Laura!

342
00:23:10.972 --> 00:23:11.973
Laura!

343
00:23:13.016 --> 00:23:14.016
Bravo!

344
00:23:14.434 --> 00:23:15.685
Good for you. Laura.

345
00:23:18.063 --> 00:23:19.606
Her speech was just great.

346
00:23:28.532 --> 00:23:30.617
And the winner is…

347
00:23:39.418 --> 00:23:40.418
Romanzy James.

348
00:23:41.545 --> 00:23:43.463
-Well done!
-Bravo!

349
00:23:44.423 --> 00:23:45.423
Bravo!

350
00:23:48.677 --> 00:23:49.677
Thank you.

351
00:23:53.932 --> 00:23:54.932
Here's to more.

352
00:24:01.022 --> 00:24:02.149
It doesn't matter.

353
00:24:03.442 --> 00:24:05.152
That was the best speech I've ever heard

354
00:24:06.278 --> 00:24:07.404
and the truest.

355
00:24:11.241 --> 00:24:13.285
What do you say we go have some music?

356
00:24:22.836 --> 00:24:23.836
All right.

357
00:25:25.398 --> 00:25:26.608
Yeah!

358
00:25:28.109 --> 00:25:29.236
This way.

359
00:25:48.213 --> 00:25:49.839
What's rattling around up there?

360
00:25:51.299 --> 00:25:54.344
You ever thought about
settling down again?

361
00:25:57.138 --> 00:25:59.432
I've tried my hand at a settled life.

362
00:26:00.559 --> 00:26:02.143
It doesn't agree with me.

363
00:26:03.937 --> 00:26:09.192
See. I think I've realized that I am…
I'm at my best when I'm part of a family.

364
00:26:14.990 --> 00:26:16.700
I wish I could give that to you.

365
00:26:39.931 --> 00:26:41.224
Can we talk?

366
00:26:41.308 --> 00:26:44.269
Just because we danced doesn't mean
I have anything to say to you.

367
00:26:45.604 --> 00:26:48.481
-You have every right to be upset.
-I'm glad we agree on that.

368
00:26:52.110 --> 00:26:53.528
You made me feel like a fool.

369
00:26:56.239 --> 00:26:58.867
-I'm sorry.
-Why didn't you just tell me?

370
00:26:58.950 --> 00:27:02.495
I don't know. I…
You caught me by surprise. I suppose. I…

371
00:27:03.288 --> 00:27:05.123
I didn't expect to fall in love again.

372
00:27:10.754 --> 00:27:13.465
I thought about you
every moment I was away.

373
00:27:15.216 --> 00:27:17.844
And I very much want you
to be part of my future…

374
00:27:20.930 --> 00:27:22.223
If you'll still have me.

375
00:27:27.771 --> 00:27:29.230
Now maybe we just…

376
00:27:31.441 --> 00:27:34.152
Have another dance for now.

377
00:27:55.632 --> 00:27:57.676
I remember the first time I saw you dance.

378
00:27:57.759 --> 00:27:59.886
I remember you barging in
with a wagon full of books

379
00:27:59.969 --> 00:28:01.489
in the middle of our cotillion lesson.

380
00:28:01.554 --> 00:28:03.973
You offered to show me the library.

381
00:28:04.057 --> 00:28:06.101
I wanted your Jane Austen.

382
00:28:06.184 --> 00:28:09.229
-Come on. I was charming.
-You certainly thought so.

383
00:28:11.940 --> 00:28:14.067
We had no idea what was ahead of us.

384
00:28:18.113 --> 00:28:19.113
Love.

385
00:28:20.198 --> 00:28:21.241
War.

386
00:28:21.908 --> 00:28:22.908
Loss.

387
00:28:24.244 --> 00:28:27.038
-Promise.
-We thought everything was possible.

388
00:28:28.915 --> 00:28:32.669
-We wanted to find a new way to live.
-It's not what I thought it would be.

389
00:28:33.920 --> 00:28:35.338
I'm not sure it ever is.

390
00:28:41.678 --> 00:28:43.138
I wanna try again.

391
00:28:44.723 --> 00:28:45.974
To start again.

392
00:28:46.975 --> 00:28:48.727
I wanna feel that promise.

393
00:28:49.769 --> 00:28:51.020
that possibility.

394
00:28:57.694 --> 00:28:58.695
You were right.

395
00:29:00.363 --> 00:29:02.115
She'll always be with us.

396
00:29:05.034 --> 00:29:06.369
no matter where we go.

397
00:29:19.549 --> 00:29:22.677
I'll. uh…
I'll talk to Louis about the farm.

398
00:29:23.720 --> 00:29:24.720
Mm.

399
00:29:47.786 --> 00:29:49.454
Hello. sweet. happy.

400
00:29:50.371 --> 00:29:51.456
Yeah.

401
00:29:53.208 --> 00:29:54.375
May I have this dance?

402
00:29:57.086 --> 00:29:58.421
We can watch Carrie.

403
00:30:11.267 --> 00:30:13.353
I know the day didn't go
exactly the way we hoped.

404
00:30:15.230 --> 00:30:16.773
It never does. does it?

405
00:30:22.529 --> 00:30:23.863
I know we can make it work.

406
00:30:26.574 --> 00:30:27.659
We always do.

407
00:30:54.227 --> 00:30:55.812
What have you done?

408
00:30:56.938 --> 00:30:59.357
What have you done? You've ruined lives.

409
00:31:00.024 --> 00:31:02.986
What are you gonna do?
You're not gonna walk away from me.

410
00:31:03.528 --> 00:31:04.528
-Hey!
-I won't.

411
00:31:04.904 --> 00:31:06.072
I'll be right back.

412
00:31:06.155 --> 00:31:08.032
Don't walk away from me. James.

413
00:31:10.285 --> 00:31:12.704
Hey! Don't you walk away from me. James.

414
00:31:12.787 --> 00:31:14.539
I said not here. Kind.

415
00:31:14.622 --> 00:31:16.958
Pay for it? I paid with my sweat.

416
00:31:17.458 --> 00:31:19.498
Leave him be. Russell!

417
00:31:19.544 --> 00:31:20.378
Hey.

418
00:31:20.461 --> 00:31:21.713
He's a snake.

419
00:31:21.796 --> 00:31:24.716
He lured us all here to watch us
get thrown out of our homes.

420
00:31:24.799 --> 00:31:27.135
Go on! Tell him. James.

421
00:31:28.344 --> 00:31:31.014
Now that the deal
with the Osage has gone through.

422
00:31:31.097 --> 00:31:33.474
the government wants
to kick us all off our claims

423
00:31:33.558 --> 00:31:35.643
unless we pay up in the next two weeks.

424
00:31:35.727 --> 00:31:38.563
-What do you mean?
-The Homestead Act isn't any good here.

425
00:31:38.646 --> 00:31:40.648
Now that they bought
the land from the Osage.

426
00:31:40.732 --> 00:31:43.151
the government wants
a return on their investment.

427
00:31:43.234 --> 00:31:47.947
Eli and his railroad sold us a lie.
and now we're left with the bill!

428
00:31:48.031 --> 00:31:49.490
I did no such thing.

429
00:31:51.326 --> 00:31:52.327
How much do they want?

430
00:31:54.120 --> 00:31:55.288
Dollar fifty an acre.

431
00:31:58.249 --> 00:31:59.334
Fair market value.

432
00:32:02.211 --> 00:32:03.588
And if I don't have it?

433
00:32:03.671 --> 00:32:06.671
The marshals will see to it that you
and me and any other fool who can't pay

434
00:32:06.716 --> 00:32:08.276
will be cleared out behind the Indians.

435
00:32:08.343 --> 00:32:11.387
Progress isn't without
its bumps and bruises.

436
00:32:11.471 --> 00:32:13.431
To hell with you and your progress.

437
00:32:24.108 --> 00:32:26.319
I could arrange a loan from the railroad.

438
00:32:27.111 --> 00:32:29.906
A foreman's salary would be
more than adequate to pay it back.

439
00:32:30.823 --> 00:32:32.659
even double your land.

440
00:32:33.451 --> 00:32:35.203
It would just be for a year…

441
00:32:37.372 --> 00:32:38.372
Maybe two.

442
00:32:40.416 --> 00:32:41.584
What do you say?

443
00:33:09.320 --> 00:33:10.697
How much did you hear?

444
00:33:11.406 --> 00:33:12.406
Enough.

445
00:33:20.790 --> 00:33:22.291
What will the harvest bring in?

446
00:33:24.002 --> 00:33:25.169
I… I don't know.

447
00:33:26.713 --> 00:33:28.172
Enough to buy ten acres?

448
00:33:30.258 --> 00:33:32.635
We could sell off some of the furniture.

449
00:33:33.511 --> 00:33:36.514
the pocket watch. the combs. the fiddle.

450
00:33:38.474 --> 00:33:41.394
If our jobs come through.
it might get us through the winter.

451
00:33:45.023 --> 00:33:47.859
Or I could take the foreman position.

452
00:33:52.488 --> 00:33:54.490
We didn't come all this way to be apart.

453
00:34:23.728 --> 00:34:24.728
What is that?

454
00:34:32.862 --> 00:34:34.072
Prairie fire.

455
00:34:34.155 --> 00:34:35.364
Let it burn.

456
00:34:35.865 --> 00:34:39.410
Let Eli's town burn to the ground.
It's what he deserves.

457
00:34:41.079 --> 00:34:43.748
Fire! Fire!

458
00:35:07.271 --> 00:35:08.356
Eli. go.

459
00:35:09.357 --> 00:35:10.357
Here.

460
00:35:11.859 --> 00:35:13.194
Take it. Be careful.

461
00:35:13.736 --> 00:35:16.030
We need to dig a firebreak!

462
00:35:32.380 --> 00:35:33.673
Fast and straight!

463
00:35:33.756 --> 00:35:37.135
Keep going! Keep going!

464
00:36:01.534 --> 00:36:03.828
They'll put it out.

465
00:36:03.911 --> 00:36:07.123
-What if they can't?
-Then we can run to the creek.

466
00:36:07.206 --> 00:36:10.251
That's where all the birds
and rabbits and snakes would go.

467
00:36:10.334 --> 00:36:12.295
Then that's where we'll run.

468
00:36:25.349 --> 00:36:27.977
♪ Let us pause in life's pleasures ♪

469
00:36:28.561 --> 00:36:30.688
♪ And count its many tears ♪

470
00:36:31.731 --> 00:36:35.484
♪ While we all sup sorrow with the poor ♪

471
00:36:36.777 --> 00:36:41.949
♪ There's a song that will linger
Forever in our ears ♪

472
00:36:42.033 --> 00:36:46.204
♪ Oh. hard times. come again no more ♪

473
00:36:47.330 --> 00:36:52.877
♪ 'Tis the song. the sigh of the weary ♪

474
00:36:53.377 --> 00:36:58.007
♪ Hard times. hard times
Come again no more ♪

475
00:36:58.090 --> 00:37:02.970
♪ Many days have you lingered
Around my cabin door ♪

476
00:37:03.054 --> 00:37:07.683
♪ Oh. hard times. come again no more ♪

477
00:37:11.395 --> 00:37:12.980
It's not working!

478
00:37:35.544 --> 00:37:37.088
We need to fall back!

479
00:37:37.171 --> 00:37:38.172
No!

480
00:37:39.340 --> 00:37:40.841
We have to keep fighting!

481
00:37:40.925 --> 00:37:43.761
No one's losing their life
for your town. Eli!

482
00:37:50.309 --> 00:37:52.061
-Get back!
-Fall back!

483
00:37:52.144 --> 00:37:53.646
-Get back!
-Get back!

484
00:37:55.189 --> 00:37:56.023
Fall back!

485
00:37:58.150 --> 00:38:00.069
Everyone. fall back!

486
00:38:01.112 --> 00:38:02.112
Come on!

487
00:38:05.950 --> 00:38:07.410
Get away from here!

488
00:38:24.802 --> 00:38:26.345
The wind is shifting.

489
00:38:31.976 --> 00:38:34.437
It's shifting! It's shifting!

490
00:39:18.898 --> 00:39:20.775
It's finally over.

491
00:39:28.741 --> 00:39:30.951
Oh. Mother. I knew I'd see you again.

492
00:39:32.453 --> 00:39:33.454
Awful.

493
00:39:34.121 --> 00:39:35.873
That was. like. awful.

494
00:39:46.342 --> 00:39:47.342
Hey.

495
00:39:48.302 --> 00:39:49.345
It's all right.

496
00:39:54.558 --> 00:39:55.558
We're safe.

497
00:39:56.477 --> 00:39:57.477
Let's go home.

498
00:40:17.998 --> 00:40:19.375
Whoa. easy.

499
00:40:28.175 --> 00:40:29.427
Jack!

500
00:40:30.344 --> 00:40:32.346
Come here. Jack!

501
00:40:35.433 --> 00:40:36.725
Let's see the damage.

502
00:40:37.643 --> 00:40:38.477
Jack!

503
00:41:01.584 --> 00:41:03.210
It's not enough to salvage.

504
00:41:04.712 --> 00:41:05.712
No.

505
00:41:09.258 --> 00:41:10.426
Where will we go?

506
00:41:13.012 --> 00:41:14.346
Back to the Big Woods?

507
00:41:17.558 --> 00:41:18.726
Is that what you want?

508
00:41:24.607 --> 00:41:26.025
I like who we are here.

509
00:41:31.447 --> 00:41:34.492
We came here to be the best versions
of ourselves. and we did that.

510
00:41:36.744 --> 00:41:37.995
We could do it again.

511
00:41:40.789 --> 00:41:41.874
Let's keep going.

512
00:41:44.543 --> 00:41:45.543
Go where?

513
00:41:51.175 --> 00:41:52.718
I'm afraid we can't stay.

514
00:41:54.553 --> 00:41:55.554
What do you mean?

515
00:41:58.599 --> 00:41:59.599
I'm sorry.

516
00:42:01.894 --> 00:42:03.687
Mary. give him the money.

517
00:42:12.279 --> 00:42:15.658
You could use this
to pay off the debt at the store.

518
00:42:20.204 --> 00:42:23.457
We didn't win as much as we hoped.
but we could get work somewhere.

519
00:42:28.212 --> 00:42:29.838
It's got nothing to do with that.

520
00:42:36.804 --> 00:42:38.013
You keep it.

521
00:42:39.098 --> 00:42:40.098
You earned it.

522
00:43:02.746 --> 00:43:03.789
Come here.

523
00:43:29.023 --> 00:43:30.691
You said this was forever.

524
00:43:35.195 --> 00:43:36.864
I wanted that to be true.

525
00:43:39.116 --> 00:43:40.743
When I imagine the future.

526
00:43:40.826 --> 00:43:42.786
when I dream about us.

527
00:43:44.913 --> 00:43:46.957
I always see the best possible outcome.

528
00:43:48.083 --> 00:43:49.293
You have hope.

529
00:43:50.669 --> 00:43:51.669
I do.

530
00:43:55.924 --> 00:43:57.551
Sometimes it's not enough.

531
00:44:20.199 --> 00:44:21.575
I'm sorry. Half Pint.

532
00:44:25.120 --> 00:44:26.955
I wish I'd done everything differently.

533
00:44:34.963 --> 00:44:36.507
Hope is everything.

534
00:44:41.553 --> 00:44:43.389
It's the only thing.

535
00:44:46.308 --> 00:44:47.601
Don't give up on it.

536
00:44:50.396 --> 00:44:51.855
Don't give up on us.

537
00:44:55.192 --> 00:44:56.192
I won't.

538
00:45:06.829 --> 00:45:09.373
Will people come to say goodbye this time?

539
00:45:11.125 --> 00:45:12.459
We'll make sure of it.

540
00:45:20.759 --> 00:45:22.428
Oh man.

541
00:45:24.012 --> 00:45:26.890
-No.
-No? Don't say it out loud.

542
00:45:27.474 --> 00:45:29.184
-We're gonna pick a date.
-Nope.

543
00:45:29.685 --> 00:45:32.062
Exactly. It stayed there.

544
00:45:40.487 --> 00:45:41.697
Where's Mr. Edwards?

545
00:45:44.158 --> 00:45:45.701
I'm sure he'll be here soon.

546
00:45:53.375 --> 00:45:55.294
It's too much.

547
00:45:56.295 --> 00:45:59.256
It's all worth three
or four times what you owe.

548
00:45:59.339 --> 00:46:00.507
We can't take it with us.

549
00:46:01.008 --> 00:46:03.510
These won't last long in the store window.

550
00:46:05.679 --> 00:46:07.389
Let me at least pay you for the plow.

551
00:46:08.098 --> 00:46:10.350
Consider anything extra
an early wedding present

552
00:46:10.434 --> 00:46:11.477
when the day comes.

553
00:46:16.356 --> 00:46:17.524
Oh!

554
00:46:21.779 --> 00:46:22.779
There we go.

555
00:46:23.822 --> 00:46:24.823
Go. go. go. go!

556
00:46:26.158 --> 00:46:27.075
Keep going.

557
00:46:29.369 --> 00:46:30.204
Yes!

558
00:46:30.287 --> 00:46:31.580
When do you ride out?

559
00:46:32.289 --> 00:46:33.707
Next week.

560
00:46:34.625 --> 00:46:35.625
You?

561
00:46:37.252 --> 00:46:38.252
Tomorrow morning.

562
00:46:47.846 --> 00:46:49.515
Thank you for your kindness.

563
00:46:52.392 --> 00:46:53.852
I hope we meet again.

564
00:47:15.541 --> 00:47:16.625
Don't forget me.

565
00:47:18.752 --> 00:47:19.752
Never.

566
00:47:45.028 --> 00:47:47.531
I'm trying to take a picture with my mind.

567
00:47:49.283 --> 00:47:50.284
Me too.

568
00:48:03.547 --> 00:48:04.798
Will you write to me?

569
00:48:06.800 --> 00:48:08.594
I like the way you see the world.

570
00:48:10.262 --> 00:48:11.805
I'll write you every week.

571
00:48:11.889 --> 00:48:13.432
I'll write you back.

572
00:48:13.515 --> 00:48:16.351
We'll have so many letters
we could make a book.

573
00:48:26.528 --> 00:48:29.156
I'll take a piece of you
with me in my heart.

574
00:48:37.623 --> 00:48:38.623
Let's go.

575
00:48:41.960 --> 00:48:44.087
The first to welcome us
and the last to say goodbye.

576
00:48:44.171 --> 00:48:46.256
Thank you for everything.

577
00:48:46.340 --> 00:48:49.676
Look after yourself. Charles.
after that family of yours.

578
00:48:50.636 --> 00:48:52.429
Be sure to steer clear of those chutes.

579
00:48:58.060 --> 00:49:00.020
He couldn't bear to say goodbye.

580
00:49:02.522 --> 00:49:04.441
But he loves you both very much.

581
00:49:09.279 --> 00:49:11.198
Tell him thank you…

582
00:49:11.281 --> 00:49:14.159
…for finding Santa Claus on the prairie…

583
00:49:17.079 --> 00:49:18.580
And for being my friend.

584
00:49:21.083 --> 00:49:22.083
I will.

585
00:50:09.006 --> 00:50:11.967
Think of how much fun
the rabbits will have eating our garden.

586
00:50:13.301 --> 00:50:14.928
Who's gonna live here now?

587
00:50:17.931 --> 00:50:20.517
Maybe a new family
looking to make their own memories.

588
00:50:23.311 --> 00:50:25.230
Maybe one
of the Osage staying behind.

589
00:50:29.901 --> 00:50:32.362
Or maybe just the flowers and sky

590
00:50:33.113 --> 00:50:34.113
and rabbits.

591
00:50:49.296 --> 00:50:53.675
♪ There is a happy land. far. far away ♪

592
00:50:53.759 --> 00:50:57.512
♪ Where saints in glory stand bright
Bright as day ♪

593
00:50:58.096 --> 00:51:02.184
♪ O. to hear the angels sing
Glory to the Lord our King ♪

594
00:51:02.267 --> 00:51:07.064
♪ Loud let his praises sing praise
Praise. praise for aye ♪

595
00:51:07.147 --> 00:51:11.485
♪ Come to the happy land
Come. come away ♪

596
00:51:11.568 --> 00:51:15.822
♪ Why were you doubting stand?
Why still delay? ♪

597
00:51:15.906 --> 00:51:20.494
♪ O. we shall happy be
When from sin and sorrow free ♪

598
00:51:20.577 --> 00:51:24.331
♪ Lord. we shall live with thee
Blest. blest for aye ♪

599
00:51:24.915 --> 00:51:27.042
Jack. come! Jack!

600
00:51:30.045 --> 00:51:32.255
Pa. stop the wagon. Stop the wagon.

601
00:51:32.339 --> 00:51:33.339
Whoa.

602
00:51:34.633 --> 00:51:36.384
Jack. come back!

603
00:51:37.052 --> 00:51:39.221
Jack! Jack!

604
00:51:43.141 --> 00:51:44.726
Jack!

605
00:51:48.396 --> 00:51:49.231
Mr. Edwards?

606
00:51:51.983 --> 00:51:53.151
It's Mr. Edwards!

607
00:51:58.990 --> 00:51:59.990
Whoa.

608
00:52:01.409 --> 00:52:03.495
Thought I might join you.
if you don't mind.

609
00:52:05.080 --> 00:52:07.207
My wife's cousin lives in Minnesota.

610
00:52:08.458 --> 00:52:11.586
Town called Walnut Grove.
Husband owns a store there.

611
00:52:12.671 --> 00:52:14.589
Heard the land is good
and the people are kind.

612
00:52:18.760 --> 00:52:21.221
-What do you think. girls?
-Yes.

613
00:52:25.225 --> 00:52:26.225
Lead the way.

614
00:52:27.310 --> 00:52:28.770
All right.

615
00:52:29.437 --> 00:52:30.437
Come on.

615
00:52:31.305 --> 00:53:31.874
Press play. Subtitles appear.
200+ languages. One app:  tryray.app
